commitResults.messageTitle: Add, List: Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Mark as Done: Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.
ToDos, Events, Deadlines: Add support for tracking three types of tasks: ToDos, Events, and Deadlines.
commitResults.messageBody:
This change uses inheritance (A-Inheritance) to allow polymorphic
storage of tasks in a single Task list while keeping type-specific
behaviors in their respective classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fixed issue where Event tasks do not show to and from values
A-TextUiTesting: Add automated text UI testing with the I/O redirection technique
commitResults.messageBody: Used the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of the chatbot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-5: Add exception handling for invalid commands and missing descriptions
commitResults.messageBody:
Added JohnException to handle exceptions exclusive to exceptions found within JohnChatBot.java
These exceptions include invalid inputs for the chatbot's commands.

commitResults.messageTitle: Delete: Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
commitResults.messageBody:
User can now delete a given taks by using the command delete <task_number> where
the task_number corresponds to the number of the task shown by running the list command.
